  "justification": "UpstreamRequest::onPoolReady in source/common/router/upstream_request.cc matches all described behaviors: it takes ownership of a GenericUpstream via move semantics, a HostDescriptionConstSharedPtr, a ConnectionInfoProvider reference, a StreamInfo reference, and an optional Http::Protocol. It calls recordConnectionPoolCallbackLatency(), moves the upstream, sets the downstream account, reports success to the outlier detector (putResult LocalOriginConnectSuccess), copies upstream connect timing data and numStreams from the pool's stream info, sets up filter state and records local/remote addresses and SSL info, syncs upstream/downstream byte meters, conditionally calls setupPerTryTimeout() or defers it via create_per_try_timeout_on_request_complete_, registers downstream watermark callbacks via addDownstreamWatermarkCallbacks, computes and starts max_stream_duration_timer_, rewrites the Authority/Host header if autoHostRewrite() is enabled and hostname is non-empty, emits an UpstreamPoolReady access log entry, and invokes onUpstreamConnectionEstablished() for all registered upstream callbacks."
}

